<p>I'm trying to track a pdf download on a webpage, following the <a href="https://developers.google.com/analytics/devguides/collection/analyticsjs/events" rel="nofollow">logic set out here</a></p>  <p>I have the following:</p>  <pre><code>$('.download-box').click(function(){   ga('send', 'event', 'pdf', 'click'); }); </code></pre>  <p>GA send has the following signature:</p>  <pre><code> ga('send', 'event', [eventCategory], [eventAction], [eventLabel], [eventValue], [fieldsObject]); </code></pre>  <p>This sends an ajax request and appears to be working.</p>  <p>The problem is the goal counter doesn't appear to register in GA reporting.</p>  <p>Here is my setup in GA admin</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/tKi0J.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/tKi0J.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>I've also tried the alternative format of ga send:</p>  <pre><code>ga('send', {   hitType: 'event',   eventCategory: 'pdf',   eventAction: 'click' }); </code></pre>